    "To answer this, in §3, we establish criteria to assess each dataset's suitability for computing explanation usefulness with the measurements overviewed in §2.",
    "We discover that 17/53 datasets are apt for studying appropriate reliance and complementary human-AI team performance but only involve low risk.",
    "4/53 additionally involve higher risk and do not have quality concerns.",
    "We recommend using these four, as high-stakes scenarios benefit more from effective explanations.",
    "We introduce the final criterion for dataset selection based on how the likelihood of hazards, and therefore risk, changes if the performance of a state-of-the-art model peaks or is so low the model cannot be collaborated with."
